Notogaster : Ratio of length to breadth 1.29 ; notogaster sub-rectangular; margins sub-parallel; caudal margin rounded, convex (Fig. 11 a). Notogastral cuticle with very small, elongate, angular alveoli ( 3–10 μm diameter;
Fig. 17
e), sparsely-distributed ( 9–17 μm apart). Setae of c -f series and p 2-3 straight or slightly curved, pointed, smooth, 59–78 μm long, except shorter seta c 1 and c 2 ( 41–44 μm). Distance between setae c 1 equal to that between c 1 and c 2 ; distance between setae c 1 0.6 × that between d 1 ; distance between d 2 1.8 × that between d 1 ; distance between e 1 0.9 × that between f 1 . Setae of h series and p 1 barbed, covered in narrow, phylliform cerotegument (Fig. 11 d). Caudal margin rounded without crenellations. Longitudinal ridge absent from either side of notogaster.

Remarks.

Novonothrus silvanus


sp. nov.

differs from other members of the genus by the following combination of characters: 
